Bundled native libraries (the packaged macOS app)
--------------------------------------------------

The packaged app bundles a shared-library FFmpeg built from unmodified
upstream sources by packaging/build_ffmpeg.sh:

  FFmpeg 8.1.2                             LGPL-2.1-or-later
    Configured WITHOUT --enable-gpl, --enable-version3, or --enable-nonfree.
    It contains no libx264, no libx265, no LAME, no opencore-amr — H.264 and
    HEVC encode through Apple VideoToolbox hardware. The same build supplies
    the bundled ffmpeg and ffprobe executables. (The upstream PyAV wheel links
    GPL x264/x265; the app deliberately does not ship it. otool -L, not
    package metadata, is the authority — see specs/09-packaging.md §3.)

Complete corresponding source for that FFmpeg: the pinned upstream tarball
(version + SHA-256) and the entire build configuration are
packaging/build_ffmpeg.sh in this repository, and each packaged release
links them from its release page. If you cannot reach either, open an issue
at https://github.com/amateurmenace/control-z and the source will be
provided at no charge.

Relinking note: the shipped app is code-signed with the hardened runtime,
which refuses a substituted libavcodec inside the signed bundle. To exercise
the LGPL relink freedom, rebuild the bundle from this repository
(packaging/) or run the tools from a source checkout — the same libraries
load unsigned there.

